14/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The chairmen of the Albanian, Croatian and Macedonian parliamentary commissions for foreign policy met in Skopje on Friday (12 May). They reaffirmed their countries' expectations that NATO's upcoming Riga summit will provide a clear signal about prospects for joining the alliance. All three countries are signatories of the US-Adriatic Charter, intended to boost co-operation in achieving the shared goal of NATO membership. In a statement, the parliamentary commission chairmen also reaffirmed their countries' determination to keep up the pace of reform and contribute to regional security. (Dnevnik - 13/05/06; A1 TV - 12/05/06)
